        <headline>Flood Advisory issued September 18 at 1:29PM AST until September 18 at 3:45PM AST by NWS San Juan PR</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive
rainfall continues.

* WHERE...Saint Croix.

* WHEN...Until 345 PM AST.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.
Water over roadways. Overflowing poor drainage areas. Ponding of
water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 129 PM AST, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. This is causing urban and small stream
flooding. Between 4 and 6 inches of rain have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 1 inch are expected over
the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Grove Place, Frederiksted South, Christiansted and
Frederiksted.
</description>
        <instruction>Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

Please report observed flooding to local emergency services or law
enforcement and request they pass this information to the National
Weather Service when you can do so safely.</instruction>
